comments: Conley (UTA) cleanly blocks Martin Jr.'s (HOU) jump shot attempt.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Conley (UTA) is already in Green's (HOU) path when marginal contact occurs as the defenders switch.
Olynyk (UTA) establishes himself in Porter Jr.'s (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs as Porter Jr. navigates over the pick.
Porter Jr. (HOU) legally contests Clarkson's (UTA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Markkanen (UTA) briefly grasps Smith Jr.'s (HOU) arm and marginal contact occurs during rebounding.
Green (HOU) and Olynyk (UTA) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs as Olynyk is securing the loose ball.
Porter Jr. (HOU) places his hand momentarily on Conley's (UTA) upper body and he immediately removes his hand as Conley elevates for the shot attempt.
Smith Jr. (HOU) is already in Fontecchio's (UTA) path when marginal contact occurs as Smith Jr. releases from the contact to roll to the basket.
Markkanen (UTA) brings his hand forward towards Gordon's (HOU) upper body, and the contact during the drive is marginal.
Olynyk (UTA) collapses his right forearm to his side, and the contact with Gordon (HOU) during his driving shot attempt is marginal.
Green (HOU) and Clarkson (UTA) come together at the same spot and briefly engage before immediately separating off ball.
Smith Jr. (HOU) and Clarkson (UTA) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs off ball.
Porter Jr. (HOU) places his hand momentarily on Clarkson's (UTA) side before immediately removing his hand.
Green (HOU) steps slightly forward towards Conley's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs at the end of the drive.  Green then cleanly deflects the ball with his forearm as Conley attempts to pass.
Conley (UTA) legally contests Porter Jr.'s (HOU) jump shot attempt.
Martin Jr. (HOU) makes contact with the ball and with the part of Clarkson's (UTA) hand that is on the ball as they pursue the rebound.
Green (HOU) steps slightly forward towards Clarkson's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Clarkson (UTA) is bracing for the contact from Green (HOU) and marginal contact occurs as Clarkson releases from the contact.

As Olynyk (UTA) pursues the rebound, his left hand makes some contact with Green's (HOU) face.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Gordon (HOU) cleanly deflects the ball away from Clarkson (UTA) during his drive.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Replay review of the out of bounds called on Gordon (HOU) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Clarkson (UTA) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Houston.
Clarkson (UTA) and Green (HOU) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Clarkson (UTA) reaches in and makes contact with Smith Jr.'s (HOU) arm, which affects Smith Jr.'s control of the ball.
Green (HOU) legally contests Clarkson's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Fontecchio (UTA) and Gordon (HOU) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Smith Jr. (HOU) and Vanderbilt (UTA) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs as Smith Jr. releases from the contact.
Vanderbilt (UTA) commits a take foul on Smith Jr. (HOU).
Martin Jr. (HOU) is moving alongside Olynyk's (UTA) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Olynyk (UTA) is bracing for the contact from Martin Jr. (HOU) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Olynyk's (UTA) pass is last touched by Clarkson (UTA) before going out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Houston.
